fields.title: About Us

fields.content:
It is important to communicate with prospective members and inform them of the benefits of becoming a member of your Association. Your website is a great place to showcase the benefits of membership to recruit new members and help member retention of your existing group.

Sample membership benefits you may want to include:

  1. Free or discounted admission to Events such as monthly luncheons, professional development seminars, and networking events.
  2. Free or discounted Job Board pricing to add or view Job Listings and Resumes.
  3. Listing in your Association's online Business Directory.
  4. Exclusive member-only content such as articles, pages, or videos. For any piece of content within Tendenci, you can define the permissions so that only certain User Groups or Membership Levels have access to that information as an added benefit.
  5. Ability to add content such as Events and Job Listings to the website. The workflow settings can be configured to require admin approval as well before content is made public.

Fill out our membership application to become a member!

fields.title: Mission/Vision

fields.content:
This theme is intended to fit the needs of most associations.

REMINDER: To edit and work on the site you will need proper permissions. So, make sure you are logged in to see all the site has to offer: /login

Check for upcoming trainings at https://www.tendenci.com/events/search/

Here are a few highlights:

  1. Stories are used for the main home page rotator as well as rotating sponsors in the sidebar. You can see the stories located here: /stories/. By using "tags" you can determine where a story is visible. For example, stories tagged "rotator" will be featured on the home page rotator, and stories tagged "sponsors" will be visible in the sidebar sponsor area.

  2. Boxes are used as content areas on the home page. You can see all of the boxes used on the site here: /admin/boxes/box/ In addition if you "roll over" a box on the home page an edit box will appear at the top. This will allow you direct access to change the text.

  3. Events are ususally the most used feature of an association website. The home page features both a list of upcoming events and also a box that will show the next event chronologically. Simply add events to the calendar and they will appear on the list with the most recent showing first. Here is the overall event calendar: /events/month/

  4. News is a list on the home page of news items in reverse chronological order posted. You can search and see the full list of news here: /news/ Simply add news items and watch them show on the list. /news/add/

  5. Business Directories are a great way to list sponsors, partners, paid business listings or other associations. You can add business directories here: /directories/add/ The business directory logos will be dynamically shown on the home page in the carousel just above the footer.

  6. Job Listings are a fantastic way for associations to make money. The home page featues a dynamic listing of open positions. Simply add jobs to the job board and the listing will show on the job board and most recent added will show on the home page. To add jobs click here: /jobs/add/

  7. Rich Media, your association can't live without it. You can add photos and videos to your site and they will feed dynamically to the home page. To add photos go to the photo albums: /photos/set/latest/ To add videos use the video module (you will need to use YouTube or Vimeo videos): /videos/

  8. Editing your Navigation is pretty easy. You can find the navigation here: /navs/ or just click edit on the link that appears when you are using the navigation.

 

Have questions? Interested in packages to build out your site?:

Contact the Tendenci Team

Tendenci - The Open Source AMS, this page will help you quickly get started on using the software. Don't forget to check out our blog posts for Tendenci news and updates. 

 

REMINDER: To edit and work on the site you will need proper permissions. So, make sure you are logged in to see all the site has to offer: LOGIN

 

An Introduction to Your Administrator Menu

After you login, the administrator menu aka Tendenci menu is where most of the software modules and settings are accessible.


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IypBkRmNFCo&feature=youtu.be

Discover Our Many Functionalities

  1. Scroll through your homepage and look for "Edit ....... Box" links.
  2. Click on these  "Edit ...Box" links to edit parts of your homepage content.

 

Give it a Test Run

  1. Click on the Mission/Vision page in the navigation under the About Tab
  2. Scroll to the bottom and click "Edit" to update the content on the page. 
 

Check out these helpful modules:

  1. Stories : Click here to update your homepage rotator images and text  (Helpfile)

  2. News :  Click here to add items to your homepage News Feed (Helpfile)

  3. Events : Click here to add events to your calendar (Helpfile)

  4. Memberships : Click here to set up automatic management of membership join/renewal (Helpfiles)

  5. Business Directories : Click here to list sponsors, partners, paid business listings or other associations. (Helpfile )

  6. Navigation: Click here to dynamically edit your navigation  (Helpfiles)
 

Feel Free to Reach out to Tendenci

If you have any questions or encountered a problem, feel free to reach out. You can post your issues on Github.
 

Have questions? Interested in packages to build out your site? Does your website engage your members?

Contact the Tendenci Team
fields.title: Here are some helpful tips for getting started!

fields.content:
Congratulations on your new site!

To get started making changes you'll need to login.

If you created this site at create.tendenci.com you already have a user account for the site and just need to set your password.

To set your password, click here to navigate to your login page and click the "Forgot Password" link.

Use the same email address that you used to create the site to reset your password.

If you did not create this site than a site super user will need to add you as a user before you can login. 

You can read more about adding new users here: https://www.tendenci.com/help-files/add-new-user-to-your-website/

fields.title: Welcome!

fields.content:
Thank you for your continued participation in our organization!

You may have received an email from us with a link to renew your membership.

If you haven't received a renewal email, please follow the directions below to renew your membership.

 

Individual Members

1. Log into the website at www.myurl.com/login

2. If you are eligible to renew your membership, you will automatically be taken to your profile on login and will see a link to renew your membership as pictured below.

3. Click "Renew your membership now" and fill out the resulting form to renew your membership.

 

Corporate/Group Membership:

If you are responsible for a corporate/group membership, please follow the instructions below to renew.

1. Log into the website at www.myurl.com/login

2. Navigate to your corporate membership in the dropdown bar at the top of the page.

3. After you click the link "My Corp. Memb.", if you are eligible to renew your corporate/organizational membership, you will see a link to renew.

 

 

Please note that only your "Corporate Member Representitive" or "Billing Representative" will have access to renew your membership. Individuals who are part of the corporate membership but not designated as the "Corporate Member Representitive" or "Billing Representative" will not have access to renew.

 

At the time of renewal you can choose to renew all individuals who are part of your corporate membership.

If you have any trouble with membership renewal or need access to be set up as a representative for your corporate/group membership, please contact us
